razerkbd: adjust hid_report_raw_event() signature for linux-zen 7.0.8+

Upstream openrazer fix (commit ef574225) guards the 6-arg call on
LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= 7.0.10. linux-zen backports the kernel API change
from 7.0.8+ but still reports as 7.0.9, so the version check misses it.
This overlay only applies to linuxPackages_zen, so unconditionally use
the 6-arg form.

--- a/driver/razerkbd_driver.c
+++ b/driver/razerkbd_driver.c
@@ -4834,11 +4834,11 @@

                             // report key down
                             xdata[1] = cur_value;
-                            hid_report_raw_event(hdev, HID_INPUT_REPORT, xdata, sizeof(xdata), 0);
+                            hid_report_raw_event(hdev, HID_INPUT_REPORT, xdata, sizeof(xdata), sizeof(xdata), 0);

                             // report key up
                             xdata[1] = 0x00;
-                            hid_report_raw_event(hdev, HID_INPUT_REPORT, xdata, sizeof(xdata), 0);
+                            hid_report_raw_event(hdev, HID_INPUT_REPORT, xdata, sizeof(xdata), sizeof(xdata), 0);
                         }
                     }
                 }
